item.title: Need help
item.dc:creator: @system system
item.description:
@system wrote:

I dont think thats anything to do with your server because the “echo off” is showing there and the “bad command or file name” is something inside your compiler.bat. Try using Mod T’s compiler or if you are, just copy and paste it again.

Or try this simple one:

@echo off COLOR 08 title YOURSERVER "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.5.0_06\bin\javac.exe" -cp . *.java "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.5.0_06\bin\java.exe" server pause

@ECHO OFF - prevent any of the commands in the batch file from being displayed

I am sorry i cant help you with the problem within your client files but maybe it will help?.. a bit…
